    dc:creator "Asakawa, Mitsuhiko" ;
    dc:date "2017" ;
    dc:title "Nippostrongylus smalesae sp. nov. (Nematoda: Heligmonellidae) collected from Maxomys whiteheadi (Rodentia: Muridae) of Sumatra, Indoneisa" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.995808>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.995810> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.995808>
    dc:description "FIGURES 1 – 7. Male of Nippostrongylus smalesae sp. nov. collected from Maxomys whiteheadi in Riau, Sumatra, Indonesia. 1. Anterior end of holotype, left lateral view. 2. Cephalic end, apical view. 3. Cross section through midbody. Arrow indicating axis of orientation of synlophe. 4. Cross section through prebursal level. 5. Posterior end of holotype, left lateral view. 6. Bursa copulatrix, severed, ventral view. 7. Distal ends of spicules and gubernaculum. Abbreviations: D. dorsal; Dl. dorsal lobe; L. left; Ll. left lobe; R. right; Rl. right lobe; V. ventral." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/995808/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.995810>
    dc:description "FIGURES 8 – 11. Female of Nippostrongylus smalesae sp. nov. collected from Maxomys whiteheadi in Riau, Sumatra, Indonesia. 8. Cross section through midbody. Arrow indicating axis of orientation of synlophe. 9. Cross section through vestibule. 10 and 11. Posterior end of allotype showing ovejector (10), right lateral view and body ridges (11), left lateral view. Abbreviations: D. dorsal; L. left; R. right; V. ventral." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/995810/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

